<br>
Kunark<br>
Burning Woods - go to the giant fort and lay waste there for a few hours.  You will make nice XP, pp, and the occasional spell.<br>
<br>
Skyfire Mountains - kill pretty much anything that moves here.  The named mobs have a bit better of a chance to drop spells though most of them will be hit or miss.  If you are feeling daring you can always tackle a guardian wurm for some of your level 60 spells.  Again rare drops.<br>
<br>
Sebilis - most of the mobs here drop either good cash item, spells, or combo of both.  You can lay waste to the exit camp if you like or head deep into seb in areas such as the discos or juggs.  Juggs have the best chance at dropping 55-59 spells though what you get can vary greatly.  There is also the chance of camping Emperor Chottal in the crypt.  He is a level 60 mob that has the rare chance of dropping level 60 spells<br>
<br>
Chardok - pretty much the same as sebilis though spell drops don't seem to be as common.  There is the chance for level 60 spells if you can get in on a Royals raid for a clerics or warriors epic.    The random chance for loot still draws people to this zone pretty much everyday.<br>
<br>
Chardok B - good spot for level 60 spells.  Need a good group, but in the 5 hours I have spent in this zone, and the plethora of mobs that are level 60, you can nab up some nice spells to either sell if you have them, or scribe.  It is however just a pocket zone so it will probably disappear within a few weeks.<br>
<br>
Veeshan's Peak - great spot for level 60 spells.  The key quest is a pain, however the reward in terms of spells is great.<br>
<br>
Velious <br>
<br>
Velks Lab - get in a upper dogs or lower dogs group and spells drop like candy along with tons of other loot.<br>
<br>
Plane of Growth  - before the POGs were back this was another great spot to get your dropped velious spells.<br>
<br>
<br>
